課程概述 Course Description
       P961400 智慧型製造系統
任課老師：李家岩 ( 3學分、開授學期：博碩上)
本課程將使學生瞭解如何應用人工智慧與資料挖礦的技術，改善製造系統的作業效率。分析模型包含了基因演算法、類神經網路、決策樹、關聯規則等，課程結合資訊與工程領域的相關知識，並藉由演算法的設計及統計的方法有系統地建模以解決實務問題。
��	1. Introduction
��	2. Computational Intelligence 
��	2.1 Simulated Annealing and Tabu Search
��	2.2 Genetic Algorithms
��	2.3 Neural Networks
��	2.4 Particle Swarm Optimization
��	2.5 Ant Colony Optimization
��	3. Data Mining
��	3.1 Principal Component Analysis
��	3.2 Decision Tree Algorithms
��	3.3 Association Rules
��	3.4 Clustering
��	4. Empirical Studies and Research Topics
P961400  Intelligent Manufacturing Systems
This course will provide students to learn how to apply artificial intelligence (AI) and data mining (DM) techniques to improve the efficiency of manufacturing systems. The models include genetic algorithm, neural network, decision tree, association rule, etc. The course integrates the knowledge domains of the information and engineering, and solves the real problem systematically using the design of metaheuristic algorithms and statistics tools.
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The objective of this course is to learn the statistics and optimization methodologies in intelligent manufacturing systems. The students will know how to apply artificial intelligence (AI) and data mining (DM) techniques to solve the real problems in shop-floor level or capacity planning problems.

Learning Requirement:
1. Know the intelligent manufacturing techniques
2. Create the prototype model to solve the problem in real setting
3. Develop the research skills and prepare a basic project report    

